## Responsive Design (Desktop-First)

### Breakpoints

TailwindCSS provides 5 default breakpoints. Use all 5 for consistent responsive design across the codebase.

```
Default (no prefix): 0px+     - Mobile phones (portrait) - Mobile-first base styles
sm:  640px  - Large mobile phones (landscape)
md:  768px  - Tablets (landscape)
lg:  1024px - Laptops / small desktops
xl:  1280px - Desktop ← PRIMARY TARGET
2xl: 1536px - Large desktops / ultrawide
```

**Note:** While TailwindCSS is mobile-first by default (base styles apply from 0px), this codebase follows a desktop-first design philosophy where the primary target is 1280px (xl breakpoint), then scaling down for smaller screens.

### Desktop-First Approach

```html
<!-- Default = Desktop (xl: 1280px), scale down for smaller screens -->

<!-- Grid: 5 columns → 4 → 3 → 2 → 1 -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-5 gap-8 
            xl:grid-cols-4 xl:gap-6
            lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-6
            md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-4
            sm:grid-cols-1 sm:gap-2">
  <div>Item 1</div>
  <div>Item 2</div>
  <div>Item 3</div>
  <div>Item 4</div>
  <div>Item 5</div>
</div>

<!-- Typography: Scale down from desktop -->
<h1 class="text-6xl font-bold 
           xl:text-5xl
           lg:text-4xl
           md:text-3xl
           sm:text-2xl">
  Page Title
</h1>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed
          xl:text-base xl:leading-normal
          md:text-sm md:leading-snug
          sm:text-xs sm:leading-tight">
  Body text scales down for smaller screens.
</p>

<!-- Spacing: Scale down from desktop (common pattern for containers) -->
<div class="px-16 py-8 m-4 space-y-6
            2xl:px-16 2xl:py-8
            xl:px-12 xl:py-6
            lg:px-8 lg:py-6
            md:px-6 md:py-4 md:space-y-4
            sm:px-4 sm:py-2 sm:space-y-2">
  Content with scaled spacing
</div>

<!-- Layout: Change direction -->
<div class="flex flex-row gap-6
            md:flex-col md:gap-4">
  <aside class="w-64 md:w-full">Sidebar</aside>
  <main class="flex-1">Main Content</main>
</div>

<!-- Container padding pattern (like navbar) -->
<div class="max-w-[1920px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 xl:px-12 2xl:px-16">
  <!-- Content -->
</div>
```

### Show/Hide by Screen Size

```html
<!-- Visible only on large desktop (2xl: 1536px+) -->
<div class="hidden 2xl:block">
  Ultrawide-specific content
</div>

<!-- Visible only on desktop (xl: 1280px+) -->
<div class="hidden xl:block lg:hidden">
  Desktop-only content
</div>

<!-- Visible only on laptop and up (lg: 1024px+) -->
<div class="hidden lg:block">
  Desktop/laptop navigation
</div>

<!-- Visible only on tablet and up (md: 768px+) -->
<div class="hidden md:block lg:hidden">
  Tablet-only content
</div>

<!-- Visible only on mobile/tablet (below lg: 1024px) -->
<div class="block lg:hidden">
  Mobile/tablet navigation
</div>

<!-- Visible only on mobile (below md: 768px) -->
<div class="block md:hidden">
  Mobile-only content
</div>

<!-- Visible only on small mobile (below sm: 640px) -->
<div class="block sm:hidden">
  Small mobile-specific content
</div>
```

### Standard Breakpoint Usage Patterns

**Container Padding (Progressive Enhancement):**
```html
<!-- Start small, scale up padding for larger screens -->
<div class="px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 xl:px-12 2xl:px-16">
```

**Grid Layouts:**
```html
<!-- Responsive grid that scales from mobile to ultrawide -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4 2xl:grid-cols-5">
```

**Typography Scaling:**
```html
<!-- Scale down heading sizes for smaller screens -->
<h1 class="text-5xl xl:text-4xl lg:text-3xl md:text-2xl sm:text-xl">
```

**Gap/Spacing:**
```html
<!-- Scale spacing proportionally -->
<div class="gap-2 sm:gap-3 md:gap-4 lg:gap-6 xl:gap-8 2xl:gap-10">
```

